 * @ingroup NTCore
 *
 * @brief Technical description of net_s as a full neural network container.
 * 
 * @details
 * This document describes net_s strictly as a structural descriptor of the network.
 * It defines layers, neurons, buffers (bff), input/output pointers, and connectivity
 * information. net_s does not execute computations by itself; all execution logic
 * is implemented externally.
 *
 * No learning, optimization, or training concepts are included here.
 *
 * @section net_concept Concept
 *
 * net_s represents the full network container. Its purpose is to store:
 * - Input references
 * - Layer definitions (first layer, optional middle layers)
 * - Neuron arrays per layer
 * - Intermediate buffers (bff) for inter-layer communication
 * - Wiring descriptors (wiring)
 * - Output pointers
 *
 * net_s is purely structural. External code iterates over layers and neurons,
 * reads inputs, applies operations (from neuron_s), and writes to outputs.
 *
